snippet.title: Top 30 Movie Endings That Don't Mean What You Think
snippet.description:
Not everything is as it seems when the credits roll! Join us as we explore film finales that are commonly misinterpreted by audiences. From the ambiguous spinning top in "Inception" to Tyler Durden's true nature in "Fight Club," these endings pack more meaning than meets the eye. Our countdown includes films like "American Psycho," "The Graduate," "Shutter Island," "Rocky," "The Shining," "Eternal Sunshine of the Spotless Mind," and more! These movies have endings with deeper meanings, hidden symbolism, or deliberate ambiguity that audiences often miss. Did you misinterpret any of these movie endings? Which of these true meanings surprised you? Let us know in the comment section.
